node.text:
Two years ago my best friend, @porsche.landon, agreed to marry me, but because of the pandemic our wedding was delayed and deposits were lost.

But that helped us learn to be patient with love. I’m sharing this today on our anniversary to tell her how excited I still am to become her husband.

Happy anniversary Porsche, and thanks again @anthonyhamiltonofficial. 

#proposal

node.title: When I Asked Porsche To Marry Me

node.text:
Can I Kick It?: After recent comments by Republican, Tim Scott, many people have messaged me asking why a Black man in America would say racism doesn’t exist here. Well, for the same reason a woman would vote for Trump, or a trans woman would fight against trans rights. Because we are all conditioned in white supremacy, patriarchy, and capitalism. But some of us actually work to uphold our oppression, whether consciously or unconsciously.

(Sharing these posts is encouraged 🥸)

#whitesupremacy #patriarchy #capitalism #antiracism

node.title: On Internalized Oppression In Oppressed Communities

node.text: There are many conversations happening about giving Andrew Cuomo his due process with an investigation into both the many accusations of sexual abuse and harassment AND his office hiding COVID-19 data about elderly homes. But people are conflating that with calls for his resignation due to a loss of public trust. Which should be familiar, as we called for the same with Republicans in similar situations. #andrewcuomo

node.title: On Due Criminal Process and Accountability to Public Trust

node.text: One major issue we have in society, especially in America, is that we have been conditioned to treat politics as we treat sports. Thus, we treat politicians as if they are our favorite players, this benefits no one other than the politicians.
